commit.message:
#227: use ``pytest_collection_finish`` to count tests: it doesn't include skipped tests.

When launched with ``--last-failed`` pytest reports all tests to ``pytest_collection_modifyitems`` but only enabled (excluding skipped) to ``pytest_collection_finish``. We must use it to report correct number of tests.

Enable tests for coverage > 5.

Support for this version was fixed in the previous two commits.
Use proxy class to implement different coverage versions.
Add support for coverage >= 5.0.1.

commit.message:
Upgrade to support latest versions, remove outdated code, fix tests.

* No 2.6, 3.5
* Pytest 4, 5 only
* Coverage 4
* Latest nose for old versions

Comment about metaInfo changed.

It said that "-k" is used to run test by name, which is not true.
See https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/PY-31836#focus=streamItem-27-3183206.0-0
Method renamed: it returns test_id + desc. For id, use test.id().

Robust way to call pylint API

Another attempt to fix #215
README: redirect to pypi for version compat
ci: better defaults for preserve compatibility (pytest version)
fix tox.ini
fix pytest version to get support on all pythons
drop 3.4 support (EOL)
pylint: fix versions
pylint: fix compatibility conditions
fix python2.6 tests

#221 subtests are broken when test has name.

We look for test name in subest.
Since id is added between test and description, we can't parse it using substring.

So, we use bare test id (without of description)
pylint: fix tests for python 2
pylint: simplify version compatibility checking, fix getting description for 2.3
Add support for PyLint >= 2.3 (#215)
Extend scope of PyLint integration tests

Retry writes to stream on a EAGAIN IOError (#213)

fixes #212

pytest: fix comparing asserts (#210)

pytest: fix truncated values in comparison failure reporting as it makes the comparison mostly useless. 

This fix overrides the truncation(s), and further improves the comparison by making it multiline (for comparing complex structures).

override pytest_assertrepr_compare to work around pytest's SafeRepr truncation
enable verbose mode to disable pytest's truncation of lines
reverse pytest's escaping of newlines (to enable multiline comparison in PyCharm)
